main event: Numerous moving unidentified targets observed on both ground-radar and air-intercept radar in Southwest Bay Labrador on September 5, 1961.
interesting points: The targets showed erratic and unpredictable movement at very high speeds, estimated between 500-600 knots.
Some of the targets remained stationary.
The targets were observed visually by the KC-97 crew, but were too fast to obtain positive identification.
The sighting was considered to indicate the presence of unusual and unidentified phenomena.
An unidentified object was also reported flying at 13,000 feet, making an abrupt left turn and passing several miles before burning out on December 31, 1961.
sighted object: numerous unidentified targets on radar and an unidentified object in the air
witnesses: military personnel operating radar and the crew of a KC-97 aircraft
